    "posts": {
      "implant-care": {
        "date": "February 12, 2026",
        "image": "https://framerusercontent.com/images/PCHp4YGU02Gr9bhVeNxl3NlwDeE.jpg",
        "title": "How to Care for Implants?",
        "content": "Dental implantation is the best way to restore a lost tooth, but its longevity is directly related to proper care. An implant, like a natural tooth, requires daily attention.\n\nFirst, it is essential to maintain meticulous oral hygiene. Use a soft brush and brush your teeth twice a day. Pay special attention to the junction between the implant and the gum.\n\nThe second important factor is the use of dental floss and special mouthwashes. This will help you remove food debris from places where the brush cannot reach.\n\nDon't forget professional cleaning at the clinic twice a year. Our specialists will use special equipment that does not damage the implant surface.\n\nFollow all the doctor's recommendations so that your new smile serves you for decades.",
        "excerpt": "Dental implantation is one of the most effective methods of modern dentistry to restore missing teeth.",
        "category": "Implantology"
      },
      "braces-timing": {
        "date": "February 25, 2026",
        "image": "https://framerusercontent.com/images/InTtVcj8vGawB5IxVzmu2I4ic.png",
        "title": "When is the Best Time for Braces?",
        "content": "Orthodontic treatment is possible at any age, but there are periods when the result is achieved more quickly and easily.\n\nFor children, the first visit to the orthodontist is recommended from age 7. At this time, jaw growth is evaluated and preventive measures are taken. However, the placement of braces themselves usually occurs between ages 11-14, when the eruption of permanent teeth is complete.\n\nAs for adults, modern dentistry offers invisible systems - ceramic braces and aligners (caps), which allow you to straighten your teeth inconspicuously.\n\nIt doesn't matter how old you are - if you want a straight and healthy smile, orthodontic treatment is for you. The main requirement is a healthy state of the gums and bone tissue.",
        "excerpt": "Many people think that braces are only effective during teenage years. In fact, that's not the case.",
        "category": "Orthodontics"
      },
      "veneers-aesthetic": {
        "date": "February 10, 2026",
        "image": "https://framerusercontent.com/images/NL9ZihxOkco4TeWtDDi8fz20.jpg",
        "title": "Veneers: The Path to a Perfect Smile",
        "content": "Ceramic veneers are thin, high-strength shells that are attached to the front surface of the teeth and radically change your smile.\n\nVeneers can solve several problems at the same time:\n1. Changing the color of the tooth that cannot be whitened.\n2. Closing gaps between teeth (diastemas).\n3. Correction of tooth shape and smoothing out minor irregularities.\n\nThe procedure requires minimal tooth processing, which makes it gentle. Veneers do not change color over time and have a luster similar to a natural tooth.\n\nAt Smile Agency, we use digital smile design, which allows you to see the future result in advance and get exactly the smile you dreamed of.",
        "excerpt": "A Hollywood smile is no longer just a privilege for stars. Veneers are the best way to achieve it.",
        "category": "Aesthetics"
      }
    },
